The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, held a press briefing where he addressed various topics including the firing of Terry Francona, the killing of Anwar al-Awlaki, and the American Jobs Act. Carney expressed support for Terry Francona and stated that al-Awlaki was a significant leader in al Qaeda who was involved in plotting terrorist attacks against the United States. He also discussed the need for Congress to pass the American Jobs Act to help stimulate the economy and create jobs.